radiographic_examinations.findings: Marked mural thickening and luminal distention of the appendix, transverse dimension 1.7 cm at the appendiceal tip; no periappendiceal fluid collections; no free fluid or gas in the abdomen or pelvis; 4 cm fat-containing hernia with 12 mm neck in the anterior abdominal wall; 3.8 cm x 2.2 cm focal area of fluid attenuation in the left adnexa, likely a follicular cyst.
